Definition: a long period of darkness and extreme cold that scientists predict would follow a full-scale nuclear war
Example: a layer of dust and smoke in the atmosphere would cover the earth and block the rays of the sun; most living organisms would perish
Synonyms: catastrophe, a, long, period, of, darkness, and, extreme, cold, that, scientists, predict, would, follow, full-scale, nuclear, war, layer, dust, smoke, in, the, atmosphere, cover, earth, block, rays, sun, most, living, organisms, perish
Category: noun.phenomenon
